			"author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
			"body": "This line [should also be changed](https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/pull/9210/files#diff-c0888183e544cf752c9e4670c6a49cde95133f607de421265bec602e28a13621R241) &mdash; without it, the `.desktop` file won't launch the AppImage:\r\n\r\n```\r\n241:            Exec=${HOME}/.joplin/Joplin.AppImage ${SANDBOXPARAM} %u\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnother thing to consider is how the `--install-dir` option will be used (e.g. whether users will try to use it to install for another user or in a global location). Currently, icons and launchers are written to locations in the user's home folder (`~/.local/share/...`). As such, what are the intended use cases for customizing the `install-dir`? Does it make sense to provide this without also changing the location of icons/`.desktop` files?",
